Hugh Segal,  (born October 13, 1950) is a Canadian political strategist, author, commentator, academic and former senator. He served as Chief of Staff to Ontario Premier Bill Davis and Canadian Prime Minister Brian Mulroney.
Segal resigned from the Senate effective June 15, 2014, prior to his upcoming appointment as Master of Massey College, Toronto for a seven-year term effective July 1, 2014.
